text: > Sports Is the SEC down? League depth a question at midway point FILE - In this Oct. 10. 2015, file photo, Georgia running back Nick Chubb is helped off the field after injuring his left knee on the first play from scrimmage during an NCAA college football game against Tennessee in Knoxville, Tenn. Chubb had been almost a surefire 100-yard runner every Saturday and was averaging 8.1 yards per carry.
